content: It's short but I like the story! fantastic!
Alter Ego Complex is so good and I really love how the story expanded more on Es and all the thing she's been through. Really hope that they add more story and multiple endings
Perfect spinoff for a perfect game

This game is so great that it makes me fall into a book with Es, mixed feelings also make this game very exciting, even though it's just a simple game but because of the storyline that makes me feel like I'm in the game so I think this game is very exciting
Cried at the end. Keep going, you'll find what I mean.
Pretty sweet story, but I do wish the messages would go a bit slower. Hard to read them all.
I would give it six stars if I could

I enjoyed the game without I doubt, they gave more in depth reading of the books from the previous game and gave a look of es in a different style of drawing and setting. It really is a great game for those of you who enjoyed alter ego. The art and writing is beautiful, and I enjoyed the mini games and systems in placed into the game. I really do wish to see more of this type of game play as the 'dreams' where a really nice touch and I would not mind paying more for such content.
A short interactive story from Es's perspective. A beautiful companion piece to Alter Ego.

Hello! I came to learn more about ES. When I was finding myself with Alter Ego, the closer I am wanting to be with ES. It's been howany months and I bought this game. It was worth to learn more. I feel sad and furious of myself. She felt like she doesn't want me to force me to be with her everyday, but becauae of this and the completion, I want to keep seeing her everyday and keep learning new experience with her or repeat the things to be with her. It was a nice interpretation. Thank you!
it's a good game

I really like this game! The way I got into it was so different from any other games, I was really confused at first but the further I go the more I understand, I'll support the developers for this great game.
This was a great and fun game.
short but sweet this game is very unique from wat ive played b4. play this after alter ego tho itll kinda make more sense
still alright
A good way to refresh my experience in its main title.
A bittersweet ending. I enjoyed playing through the game. Maybe just lower the price a bit, the story was a bit short.
amazing. love these games.
Cute follow-up to Alter Ego! I enjoyed seeing more of Em's perspective.
Simply wonderful. I wish I could meet Es as well. Give her the life she dreamt about. But alas, some things are not meant to be. Farewell dear Es.
Need more content.

I was a bit disappointed honestly. I can't rate it too low, cause I love Es, but this game was too short, there wasn't much to do, the mini-games were too simple and boring for very little reward, and you really don't get to explore Es like in the first game. I bought it on a sale so I didn't use much money, but I still feel like the original game was worth so much more than this one. It was decent, but they didn't even have any books that weren't in the original game. 3/5, very disappointed.
We need more of this wholesome stuff as well as more interaction with es in the actual alter ego.

It's funny to fall in love her. Considering you're gonna sympathize with her. The saddest part is when you do finish this and even more so when you think about your mortality. There will come a day when she realizes that she's technically immortal in her own story so to speak. To Caramel Column Inc be nice if she had a name and also if she realizes that she's a character in her game or story lol
Thank you for the experience. Artwork, music, Es and a reminder to visit her more often. I loved each minute of it.
Chilled, relaxed, exactly why I bought it.
yep, really put you on Esu Perspective. great job
That was it? It's not exactly worth paying $7 for. Maybe $3 sure. The graphics are nice. The gameplay was simple. Just couldn't help that this could have been so much more.
Feels good spending time together with Es, and know about her more.
astounding i just cant wait for more series to come
good but too short

For what it is, I'm glad this was made and what it is. I still play the original game, but this one truly made me think about what goes on when I'm not. It goes further in depth about Es and her character, and i'm glad I'm able to experience this.
A short-lived dream, I can only hope to see more from Es in the future.

Uuh devs thank you so much bruh bruh bruh, i already prepared my money today to paid this game today but bruh bruh bruh you devs gives us an absolute discount thank you so much bruh bruh bruh P O G °O°
This was an amazing experience and a emotional ride, sadly it's so short yet feels long, I completely love it

Honestly, the game is very well-made and discusses Es' character very well, but it's very slow and the gameplay is quite boring and repetitive. I'm glad I bought it when it was on sale because it was really short and I feel as if the original price wasn't very fair. The game is wonderful though. Thank you for this experience.
Es best girl
Masterpiece
its a great story, a bit short but plenty of emotion

Well it's a short and bittersweet game. I got to delve into books with Es and listen to more of her thoughts and see her dreams, and the post completion scenario in the other game brings the same emotion. I can understand why people feel that it costs a bit much, but the creators need to earn their keep and ads would certainly mess with the immersion so I won't comment on that. I certainly hope for more things to come, and that we'll learn a little more about this lonely world.
Great game as usual
A short, but pleasant addition to the original. incredibly thankful I got it
So much backstory is explained about ES and you finally get to know her better as well as understand her motives. As always a very good game and definetly worht my money and time!
It was simple and beautiful. No personality tests but mainly because it is a story of Es. Es is herself and not a shadow of anyone else.
It was short yet a great experience
Spin-off game, like an add on from the original
Just like Alter EGO it pulls at the heartstrings in the most delightful way. Well done dev team!
Highly recommend that you should play the first version of this game, so you can understand the second one fully. It's a well-built story & emotions game.
It was lovely. I was always curious what she did in her time alone when we had left.
Interesting backstory, but not as interesting as the Alter Ego story.
I don't know how to feel about this, really..
If you loved the first AE then you will love this one as well. Kudos to the creators!

So I saw Es's life in her world. Reading books, and asking questions. That was nice, it gave extra understanding of Es. It was short, but I like it though. Apart from is this game worth buying, I am happy to give it 5 stars.

it really explains the last game by another view point and makes us understand what is like living like Es. but be warned it is like a "spin-off" of the last game being very sort and you need to play the other. i recommend this fo those who liked the last one an would like a little more of what they had in the first one.

I fell in love with the first Alter Ego and plunged right into this one as soon as I finished. I really enjoyed seeing things from Es' thoughts as she dreamed of the books she read and her desire to be with The Wanderer. If you enjoyed the first Alter Ego, you'll certainly enjoy this as well! Hope to see more!
Amazing and beautiful.
I never quite understood how Es felt in the first game. It's a sad story, but also a happy one. It's honestly a masterpiece and worth the time and money.
What a beautiful game, loved getting to know more about Es! Great job to the developers! :)
Beautiful music

Unlike its predecessor, it seems the team hasnt found a way to turn this style of bare bones, repetitive gameplay into something engaging. While its predecessor tread more meditative, the incredibly short and mundane play with minimal story revealed kept dragging my mind back to the $7 price tag, even as I was trying to enjoy seeing Es again. I'm still a fan of the team, and want to see more from them, but perhaps they should have considered integrated ads instead for this installment.

This game brings with it joy and peace of mind. I can count on it to brighten my day and jump start an optimistic outlook on life. I've enjoyed every moment, every replay, and every continuation made since its original creation. I highly recommend playing this series.

This game is great. Short but great. Like another user said, I grew emotionally attached to Es and it does hurt right in the beating heart knowing she's not real. I hope you guys keep making more ALTER EGO games. Great game, fantastic writing, it feels so immersive. Keep up the great work, guys.
i love it, its worth the money
i bought it so i can discuss it with Es in the first game..
beautiful story with some actual gameplay
Short but beautiful. Admittedly the mini games were unnecessary. Regardless if you loved Es then go for it as it's more content featuring her.

I was so excited for this because I absolutely loved Alter Ego. I went in expecting so much because the first game was so so good but I was slightly disappointed, I really thought it would vastly expand on the world of Es but nar. We get dream clips and so forth but I felt so sad about the progression, I mean from the main game to this. I wanted to interact with Es fully and see the world through her eyes. For the £6.99 price tag, I felt abit ripped off tbh
Make more games , i love it
excellent game. 10/10
a great abstract story, really give you the feeling that you didn't feel in previous story. probably one of masterpiece of storytelling
lovely game the main issue is that for how short it is it's overpriced. but other than that perfect. It really makes me feel bad about the day's I forget to visit ES
loved it<3

A little too short, but still one of the best games I have ever played. Es is just an amazing character. It may sound weird, but I grew up to get attached-emotionally- to her. Sometimes it hurts knowing that she will never be real, which is kind of ironic.

Very well done and expands on the story told in Alter Ego. Very simple clicking and tap games but I feel that there could have been more available as well as more books to walk through. Hopefully that gets added (would love some of the books you borrow at the end game of Alter Ego) as well as more dreams we can find because outside them there isn't much to honestly justify the price tag. A bit expensive but worth it if you've gone through all of the base game.

It hit incredibly close to home when my depression was at its worst and I spent all day just daydreaming or trying to sleep so I could dream more. It captures the feeling of loneliness and all the thoughts you get with depression so well; it's an incredible sequel. The only complaint is is that it's so short and there aren't much things to do.

An interesting twist on the gameplay. It's a different narrative with a more personalized tale on Es herself. if you love the story of alter ego and the fictional character Es, then this story is for you.
maybe all I want is just the sound of piano in the quiet night afterall.

a great game for people who loved the first game, and especially Es! it's good game with an amazing soundtrack and art, and it shows how Es' thought process behind everything. if you don't particularly feel attached to Es, then it may not be worth the price. if you do like Es a lot though, you should by this game!!
I agree with most that it is a bit short, but I also understand why they made it that way. Though I hold no illusions to meeting the character that is Es. I do hope to one day find my Es.

as expected, the game did not disappoint. I'm not one for buying games but if you loved the first game as much as I did, this expense was worth it. i really hope we get to see more of es in the future.

I love how it expands on Es's character. The first game was great, giving life to a character I wasn't sure I'd feel for. The second one was short and I'm barred from finishing the game, as I've gotten through all the books, except the last one. I don't know how to unlock that one. Game was short and sweet. Loved seeing her dreams. Definitely recommend both for quite the immersive story.
the alter ego complex is very great.

Beautifully written - wonderful story from the viewpoint of Es. Was pretty disappointed by how short it was compared to the original Alter Ego (gotta say, I expected a lot more for $7), but I have a feeling that there's more to come. The art and music are also spectacular as always.
NO NO NOOOOO I CAN'T WAIT FOR Es ANYMORE I WANT TO MEET HER PLEASE TELL ME WHERE SHE LIVES... //(btw I'm just joking)

A beautiful game but very very short. You will most likely complete it in one sitting. You might want to wait for a sale for this one, but if you liked the story of the first this is a lovely chapter. The art and music are as charming as ever.
Excellent development for Es. I loved it all the way through.

Writing this right after finishing it, like last time. Just like last time, this game made me feel understood in a way I never thought was possible. I took so many screenshots of the book quotes so I could write them down and read them whenever I felt conflicted or sad. The music, too, was so fresh and new, yet reminiscent of Alter Ego and its events. It felt like I was given the window into Es' heart that I had been wishing for for so long. Playing this was just what I needed today. Thank you.
This game is 100% for people in love with the first game, "Alter Ego", as this is a spin off. Best girl for mobile (in my humble opinion) is in this game ^_^
I love this very much, I'll wait if there are more of your creation in the future. I will support you the best I can.
Noice

True to what people have said, this game IS short. But the way it's executed is done so well. For anyone who played the original ALTER EGO and/or felt really attached to Es, you'll most likely thoroughly enjoy this. And yes, it's meant for the people who played the original (and likely all the way through at that). It still keeps the charm from the original game and that really tops this game off. If it were me rating the game out of 10, like ALTER EGO, this would warrant a 10/10. Kudos to these devs.

This game covers what Es does in the absence of the Wanderer. It's a sad story that covers Es's repetitive routine as she re-reads the books in her room, asks herself questions based on the book she's reading, then drifts to sleep where she dreams her innermost wishes. It's a very short lived experience, the game hardly lasts for 30 min including the mini-games and the last book Es reads. Comparing this to Alter Ego is unfair; it's merely a simple yet sad side story.

Deeply disappointing. I loved the original Alter Ego and adore the character of Es, and for such a strong game to be followed by this is depressing. The writing is good, but it's as if they forgot to make it a game. It's more of an unending slog through the slowest form of reading and clunky copies of Angry Birds all in order to earn a piece of information about Es' feelings. It's a painful experience, not in the good way, and not worth any money at all.

Complex is an overall fantastic game that is a must-have for all who enjoyed the first Alter Ego. It really gives a lot of background on Es' character which we still know very little about. The artstyle varries a bit from the previous game, but it can undoubtedly be recognized as part of Alter Ego. I really hope that Complex is the second game of many to come, as the game itself was rather short. In the meantime, I'm crossing my fingers that Alter Ego will live on!
A dream Or not a dream?
This game is absolutely beautiful. I highly recommend to play Alter Ego before this. Otherwise the story might not make sense.
I thoroughly enjoyed the story! It really did add more depth to the original game. Great job!
Wonderful game. Although it's short, it really sheds more light on Es' life. I recommend you try the original game first before playing this; however, I insist you download this game afterwards.

Maybe the original games set the bars way too high for anything AlterEgo related. Considering also how long I have waited for this. Really disappointing, I kinda want something more. I guess I paid for some wallpapers and pics of Es.

Alter Ego Complex is just as beautiful as the first game. It is quite short, only 30 minutes to an hour but every second feels worth it if you enjoy the character of Es. To me it was worth the price and I think that if you thoroughly enjoyed Alter Ego as I did, you will not be disappointed by Complex. The developers have done a fantastic job once again and I look forward to see what they have planned for the future.
Quite possibly one of the better dlc that Alter Ego has to offer. The gameplay at first was relatively slow however, it became rewarding near the end. Truly a great experience for one to enjoy.
Fun game but please make it longer or add more features...
Worth the wait. Seeing Es in her many forms is really lovely. Well done as always.
Short but sweet. It supplements the main story very well.
A truly beautiful game. It isn't as long as I hoped it would be, but I feel that its length fits the narrative perfectly.
very interesting. I wouldn't say fun but worth it if you want gorgeous music and a continuation of the story.

Simple yet tranquil art style, soothing yet familiar soundtrack, but short storyline with a 2$(in my country) price tag. Its a fan service for people who enjoyed Alter EGO and want something different but the 2$ price tag for something like this, maybe decrease the price tag into 1.30$ or just make it free and add some ads and other things just like Alter EGO did, thats a better (or reasonable) price tag. Haven't found bugs or anything broken. Nice game.
Love it, only complain is its short

Once more Alter Ego delivers on it's unique brand of somber melancholy. I'm probably gonna jg to be visiting Es in the base game more often again. Complex is a shorter experience devoid of the clicker padding from the original. This is both a good thing and a bad thing.

I cannot express the following point enough, this game is meant to be played and enjoyed by those who not only finished the prior game (alter ego) but ache to know more about its central character, only when viewing the game like this can one truly enjoy it for its more laid back contemplative gameplay which centers around learning and understanding the feelings of the main character, though its short it's an experience that has the ability to move the player deeply.

Music and art is as beautiful as the first game. Complex is simple but lovely. Although it was a little short, I have faith that this isn't the end. I think there will be an update or ending of some sort someday. One where Es does go free at the cost of us never being able to see her again. That's fine with me. Although this is just my wishful thinking. I'll keep dreaming about that happy ending.
The content itself was good and a lot of effort clearly went into the art, but the entire game is only like 30 minutes...

I really loved seeing Es in a new light but I think the game was pretty damn short, I think it would be cool if maybe extra content got added in the future to either this or alter ego and maybe gave Es a happy conclusion such as her finally leaving the library and living a happier life
It was a nice love letter to fans of the game
BEST JUST ABSOLUTELY THE BEST, tho the jumping rabbit part was a little clunky but all in all this game is just mwah 5 star

Beautiful. This series is an incredible work of art. I hope that one day the creators can expand the world of Es. She can't come to our world, so we should just make her own world. Anyway, great addition to an already known masterpiece.
I loved Alter Ego, and this was a nice spinoff. I do think it was a bit short, but im glad this universe is being expanded upon.
It's a crime how short this game is

As someone who really loved the original game, this came out as a disappointment. It was a good and beautiful game, but it was way too short, and definitely not worthy of all the time I waited for it, or the money I've spent. I really hoped for something better.

Thank you so much for this game! I really love Es and missed her so much too (I cried countless times while playing it). I love Es's dreams. And when I updated Alter Ego, there was a new conversation with Es waiting for me!! This time she held my hand (cries again). I love this game and you developers who made it. Thank you so much!
If you've played the first game, then you're in for a treat. You'll be exploring more about Es as a dreamer. The Hare of Inaba minigame can be tough, but you just have to time your taps.
Happy Es in her dreams gave warmth to my heart, but in the end only depression stayed by my side.
Amazing and beautiful is all i can say. Normally i don't buy mobile games, but this game i bought without hesitation. I hope to see even more from this studio.
3 words. Sailor. Uniform. Es.
